# Cursor.ai Cursors Rules for WaterWise Project

## Project Overview
This project is a web application built using the latest .NET version for the backend and Angular for the frontend, incorporating Signals and RxJS for reactive programming.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: .NET (latest version)
- Frontend: Angular, Signals, RxJS, TypeScript
- Database: SQL Server
- Testing: MSTest, NUnit, Karma
- CI/CD: Azure DevOps
- Code Quality: StyleCop, ReSharper
- Package Management: NuGet
- Version Control: Git

## General Rules
- Do not add comments that state the obvious

## Frontend Rules
- Use reactive programming with RxJS and Signals.
- Use Angular CLI for efficient development and scaffolding.
- Use Angular Material for UI components.
- Use Angular Flex Layout for responsive design.
- Use Angular Reactive Forms for form handling.
- Use Angular Router for navigation.
- Use Angular Services for shared functionality.
- Use Lazy loading
- Use control flow

## Development Guidelines
- Follow best practices for .NET and Angular development.
- Ensure code is clean, maintainable, and well-documented.
- Use appropriate design patterns and architectural principles.
- Implement unit tests for critical components and ensure high test coverage.
- Maintain a consistent coding style across the project, adhering to the defined EditorConfig settings.

## Deployment
- Use Azure for hosting and deployment.
- Ensure all sensitive information is secured and not hard-coded.
- Automate deployment processes using CI/CD pipelines.
- Monitor application performance and health metrics post-deployment.

## Collaboration
- Use Git for version control and follow branching strategies.
- Conduct thorough code reviews for all pull requests.
- Maintain clear and open communication within the team.

## Performance
- Optimize application performance and scalability.
- Regularly profile and analyze application performance metrics.

## Security
- Implement security best practices to protect user data.
- Regularly update dependencies to mitigate vulnerabilities.
- Conduct security audits and code reviews focusing on security aspects.

## Additional Considerations
- Utilize Angular CLI for efficient development and scaffolding.
- Leverage RxJS for managing asynchronous data streams effectively.
- Ensure that all components are reusable and follow the DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principle.
